author: Emily Green
title: Prop. I, Mission building initiative, elicits emotional arguments
text:
Photo: Josh Edelson, JOSH EDELSON / SAN FRANCISCO CHR Proposition I opponent Sonja Trauss speaks about market rate housing and how it may affect the area in the Mission district of San Francisco on October 12, 2015. Proposition I opponent Sonja Trauss speaks about market rate...
René Yañez, who has lived in the Mission for 35 years, sees the effects of gentrification all over his neighborhood. “See this place: expensive hipster,” he said, pointing to a restaurant at 24th and Valencia streets. Strolling nearby alleys, he points to colorful murals and warns, “If rich people buy this and build condos, all this is going to go away.” Proposition I opponent Sonja Trauss speaks about market rate housing and how it may affect the area in the Mission district of San Francisco on October 12, 2015.
